parse: Verb - Aorist Imperative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: Answer, bid, bring word, command. A primary verb; to speak or say.
Archippus, a Christian of Colossae. From arche and hippos; horse-ruler; Archippus, a Christian.

parse: Verb - Present Imperative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: (primarily physical), I look, see, perceive, discern. A primary verb; to look at.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.

parse: Verb - Present Subjunctive Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: From pleres; to make replete, i.e. to cram, level up, or to furnish, satisfy, execute, finish, verify, etc.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Waiting at table; in a wider sense: service, ministration. From diakonos; attendance; figuratively aid, service.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 2nd Person Singular
str2: From para and lambano; to receive near, i.e. Associate with oneself; by analogy, to assume an office; figuratively, to learn.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
Lord, master, sir; the Lord. From kuros; supreme in authority, i.e. controller; by implication, Master.
